<h2>
    <strong>Frequently Asked Questions</strong>
</h2>
<p>
    <strong>1. When is the best time for rainbow trout fishing near Portland?</strong><br>
    Spring and fall are the most productive seasons, especially just after fish stocking events.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>2. Do I need a fishing license for kids?</strong><br>
    Children under 12 do not need a license. Ages 12–17 require a youth license.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>3. Can I keep the trout I catch?</strong><br>
    Yes, but always check current bag limits and size restrictions.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>4. Are there any fly-fishing-only waters nearby?</strong><br>
    Yes, several river sections are restricted to fly fishing only—check ODFW regulations.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>5. What’s the best bait for stocked rainbow trout?</strong><br>
    PowerBait and nightcrawlers are most effective, especially shortly after stocking.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>6. Are there any free fishing weekends in Oregon?</strong><br>
    Yes! Oregon offers a few weekends each year when no license is required—usually in February and June.
